{"key":"processedPost-16223211","value":{"id":16223211,"first":16209695,"last":16224269,"when":1336914021,"utime":"05/13/12 04:00 PM","content":"For a bulk substrate that size, don't use saran wrap.&nbsp; <br />Cover the tray with foil and crimp it around the edges.&nbsp; You'll get lots of gas exchange because the seal of the foil isn't airtight.&nbsp; Also, I'd poke about half a dozen holes in the foil to boot.<br />The original poster has drowned the mycelium with a too-wet substrate and cut off its air supply by only having one hole, and it's taped up.&nbsp; If a BRF jar needs four holes for gas exchange, it only makes sense a bulk substrate would need around ten or more times the number of holes.<br />RR","title":"Re: Substrate Problems"}}